article.headline: Gardner-Webb 64, Charleston Southern 61
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- Jonathan Moore scored 13 points and Thomas Staton had four of his six points in the game's final minute, leading Gardner-Webb to a 64-61 win over Charleston Southern on Thursday night. Joshua Henley added 12 points and Auryn MacMillan had 10 for the Runnin' Bulldogs (4-10, 1/3 Big South Conference), who snapped a 10-game losing skid. Coming into the game, Gardner-Webb hadn't won since Nov. 21. With the score tied at 58-all and 1:30 left on the clock after a Gardner-Webb timeout, Staton dropped in a layup for his team's first lead since 5 minutes into the contest. The Runnin' Bulldogs went 4-for-4 from the foul line in the final 25 seconds before Jeremy Sexton's late 3 pulled the Buccaneers within the final margin. Kelvin Martin scored 21 points to lead the Buccaneers (7-8, 2-3), while Sexton finished with 18.
